{"session_id":"svc-1780715253895136759","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-06-06T03:07:35.574726344Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-ef86a116-20260606T030652-9005402a","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-ef86a116\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eexecute-bead: narrow main-git lock surface — exclude worktree creation in pre-dispatch and merge work in Land from the critical section\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM: The DDx main-git lock (`.ddx/.git-tracker.lock`,\u0026#xA;`cli/internal/agent/tracker_lock.go`) is held across operations that do\u0026#xA;not require atomic serialization. The two worst offenders are\u0026#xA;pre-dispatch (`execute_bead.go:1493-1524`) and Land\u0026#xA;(`execute_bead_land.go:1210-1216`). On a niflheim-sized repo under disk\u0026#xA;contention, the held region can exceed the 30s\u0026#xA;`MaxElapsed` lock-wait budget, causing sibling workers to time out at\u0026#xA;`withTrackerLockPolicy` line 205 (\u0026#34;max elapsed\u0026#34;) and the loop to\u0026#xA;misclassify the timeout (sibling bead ddx-2189a07f).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE: Two regions hold the lock around work that is sequencing,\u0026#xA;not critical section:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  Pre-dispatch at `execute_bead.go:1493-1524`:\u0026#xA;  - commitTrackerLocked(projectRoot)             — needs lock (writes .ddx/beads.jsonl + commits)\u0026#xA;  - checkpointPreDispatchDirt(projectRoot, ...)   — needs lock (commits on branch)\u0026#xA;  - resolveBase(gitOps, projectRoot, ...)         — read-only ref resolve; reads must observe the commits above\u0026#xA;  - attemptBackend.Prepare(...)                   — creates worktree via `git worktree add --detach \u0026lt;wt\u0026gt; \u0026lt;baseRev\u0026gt;`; writes per-worktree state under .git/worktrees/\u0026lt;id\u0026gt;/ — NO shared-state conflict with sibling workers\u0026#39; Prepare()\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  Land at `execute_bead_land.go:1208-1216` calls `landLocked` which\u0026#xA;  performs (per `:1218-1259` and beyond):\u0026#xA;  - resolve target branch, target ref, current tip                 — read-only\u0026#xA;  - countContributingCommits / preserveIfLargeDeletion              — read-only / preservation stash\u0026#xA;  - ensureLandingWorktreeReady                                       — sets up a temp worktree\u0026#xA;  - the actual fast-forward / merge commit on target branch         — needs lock (ref update)\u0026#xA;  - dirty-path sync to operator checkout                             — outside merge correctness\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  In both cases the ONLY operations that race with sibling workers are\u0026#xA;  the ref/tracker writes. Reads can be ordered by re-resolving after\u0026#xA;  reacquiring the lock if the write decision depends on them.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The conservative lock placement appears to be defensive rather than\u0026#xA;correctness-required. There is no comment at either call site explaining\u0026#xA;why worktree creation or merge prep must be inside the lock, only the\u0026#xA;single-line claim at `execute_bead.go:1489-1490` that the lock is \u0026#34;held\u0026#xA;only across the brief pre-dispatch sequence (~1-2s)\u0026#34; — which the\u0026#xA;observed 30s timeout disproves.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A) Pre-dispatch (`execute_bead.go:1493`):\u0026#xA;   1. Keep `commitTrackerLocked` and `checkpointPreDispatchDirt` inside\u0026#xA;      the lock (they write).\u0026#xA;   2. Move `resolveBase` to immediately after lock release (it\u0026#39;s a\u0026#xA;      read; if the resolution must observe the writes above, the\u0026#xA;      release+resolve sequence guarantees that on POSIX FS — git\u0026#39;s own\u0026#xA;      ref reads see the latest committed refs without a lock).\u0026#xA;   3. Move `attemptBackend.Prepare(...)` entirely outside the lock.\u0026#xA;      Workers will race their `git worktree add` calls; git\u0026#39;s per-\u0026#xA;      worktree locks (`.git/worktrees/\u0026lt;id\u0026gt;/HEAD.lock`) handle the\u0026#xA;      brief internal contention safely.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;B) Land (`execute_bead_land.go:1210`):\u0026#xA;   1. Split `landLocked` into a read-prep phase (resolve target,\u0026#xA;      currentTip, contribCount, preserveIfLargeDeletion,\u0026#xA;      ensureLandingWorktreeReady) that runs OUTSIDE the lock and a\u0026#xA;      ref-update phase (the actual fast-forward or merge commit) that\u0026#xA;      runs INSIDE the lock.\u0026#xA;   2. Inside the lock, re-resolve `currentTip` and verify the prep-phase\u0026#xA;      decision is still valid (target branch hasn\u0026#39;t moved). If it has\u0026#xA;      moved, release and retry the prep phase. This is the classic\u0026#xA;      optimistic-locking shape.\u0026#xA;   3. The dirty-path-sync to operator checkout at end of `landLocked`\u0026#xA;      runs outside the lock; it touches the operator\u0026#39;s working tree,\u0026#xA;      not shared refs.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;C) Ancestry checks (`execute_bead_land.go:839`, `857`):\u0026#xA;   - `FetchOriginAncestryCheck` does network I/O under the lock. The\u0026#xA;     comment says it is reserved for `ddx sync` and not called from\u0026#xA;     drains — verify and, if confirmed, leave as-is (sync is operator-\u0026#xA;     driven and contention there is acceptable). If the call site is\u0026#xA;     reached from drains, remove the network I/O from the locked\u0026#xA;     region.\u0026#xA;   - `LocalAncestryCheck` is read-only; remove the lock entirely or\u0026#xA;     keep only for read-after-write ordering with adjacent writes.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;D) Section labels:\u0026#xA;   - This bead depends on ddx-69a9ecd3 (lock observability), which adds\u0026#xA;     a `section` parameter to `withMainGitLock`. After that lands, the\u0026#xA;     narrower critical sections should use distinct sections\u0026#xA;     (\u0026#34;pre_dispatch_commits\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;land_ref_update\u0026#34;) so the metric reflects\u0026#xA;     the change.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE:\u0026#xA;- Changing the lock retry policy.\u0026#xA;- Changing tracker-write semantics or .ddx/beads.jsonl layout.\u0026#xA;- Cross-process IPC for coordination beyond the file-based lock.\u0026#xA;- Eliminating the lock entirely (the writes still need serialization).\u0026#xA;- Concurrent worktree-creation perf — git handles that.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;IN-SCOPE FILES:\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go (lines 1485-1530 region)\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land.go (lines 1200-1340 region; the\u0026#xA;  function `landLocked` and its callers)\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land.go (lines 839, 857; ancestry\u0026#xA;  call sites — verify drain-loop call paths first)\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_test.go and\u0026#xA;  cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land_test.go (tests for the\u0026#xA;  narrowed-lock contract)\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;OUT-OF-SCOPE FILES:\u0026#xA;- tracker_lock.go (no change required; the API supports a narrower\u0026#xA;  region without code change)\u0026#xA;- durable_audit.go (already minimal — only commit ops; do not touch)\u0026#xA;- preservePreDispatchDirtyPathsLocked at execute_bead.go:694 (already\u0026#xA;  minimal — stash ops only; do not touch)\u0026#xA;- cmd/* (no change to CLI surface)\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... -run \u0026#39;TestPreDispatch.*LockSurface|TestLand.*LockSurface|TestConcurrentPrepareNoLock|TestConcurrentLandRefRace\u0026#39; -count=1` passes.\u0026#xA;2. A unit test asserts attemptBackend.Prepare runs without holding withMainGitLock (the test injects a sentinel that fails if called inside the locked region).\u0026#xA;3. A unit test asserts landLocked\u0026#39;s read-prep phase (resolveRef, countCommits) runs without holding the lock; the ref-update phase still does.\u0026#xA;4. A concurrent test launches two synthetic workers that exercise pre-dispatch + Land in parallel and asserts neither times out on a 5s MaxElapsed budget (proves the narrowed lock holds ≪5s).\u0026#xA;5. A unit test asserts the optimistic-retry path in landLocked: when currentTip changes between read-prep and re-resolve, the prep phase is re-run rather than returning a stale-ref error.\u0026#xA;6. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./... -count=1` passes (full suite — landing is core).\u0026#xA;7. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:agent, area:execution, kind:perf, kind:reliability, phase:iterate, spec:FEAT-010\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"8e3cfb284094e8d3697764e531e51e0f8bd3c5fa\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260606T030652-9005402a\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-010\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md\"\u003eFeature: Task Execution\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-ef86a116-20260606T030652-9005402a/.ddx/executions/20260606T030652-9005402a/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-ef86a116-20260606T030652-9005402a/.ddx/executions/20260606T030652-9005402a/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik